🎬 MovieApp

MovieApp is a modern iOS application that allows users to browse, search, and favorite movies. It follows the MVVM architecture and utilizes the Combine framework for data binding and reactivity.

📌 Features

🎞️ Fetch and display popular movies.

🔍 Search movies dynamically.

❤️ Add/remove movies from favorites.

📜 Detailed movie information.

🎨 Modern and minimalistic UI.

🛠️ Tech Stack

Language: Swift

Frameworks: UIKit, Combine

Architecture: MVVM

Networking: URLSession, Combine

📂 Project Structure

MovieApp/
│── Model/            # Data models
│── ViewModel/        # Business logic and API calls
│── Views/            # UI components and ViewControllers
│── Services/         # API and Network Layer
│── Extensions/       # Reusable extensions
│── Resources/        # Assets, fonts, etc.
│── Tests/            # Unit tests

🚀 Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/iosdevashu177singh/movieapp.git

Navigate to the project directory:

cd movieapp

Install dependencies using CocoaPods:

pod install

Open the .xcworkspace file:

open MovieApp.xcworkspace

Build and run the project in Xcode.

📡 API Integration

This app fetches data from The Movie Database (TMDB) API.
Make sure to add your API Key in APIService.swift:

private let apiKey = "9a7243213d79e4344f8f16ce3b6098cf"
you can use your own.

🧪 Unit Testing

Run unit tests using:

Cmd + U (in Xcode)

Test cases are included for API calls and ViewModel logic.

